\fBOptions which are not saved: \fR
.br
\fB -delf, --deletefax\fR: delete a fax with query\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -delo, --deleteorphans\fR: delete entries from `\fBspool\fR` without detection of file in waiting directory or capisuite fax or hylafax\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -dela, --deleteallwaiting\fR: delete all waiting faxes and associated entries from `\fBspool\fR`\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -again, --receiveagain\fR: present a received fax again\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -red, --redirect\fR: redirect outgoing fax ahead by the other channel\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -csf, --correctsuccessflag\fR: in the database table `\fBouta\fR` the success flag is being corrected\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -rod, --reorderdir\fR: Examine files in waiting,failed a.faxed directory against the tables `\fBouta\fR` and put them to order\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -st, --stop\fR: stop autofax2\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -listo, --listoutg\fR: lists entries from `\fBouta\fR` with success flag\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -listf, --listfailed\fR: lists entries from `\fBouta\fR` without success flag\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -listi, --listinca\fR: lists entries from `\fBinca\fR`\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -listw, --listwaiting\fR: lists waiting faxes\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -s, --search <string>\fR: Look in processed faxes for <string>:  ('\fB\fR')
.br
\fB -n, --reccount <string>\fR: No. of listed entries = <no> instead of ('\fB30\fR')
.br
\fB -vc, --vc\fR: edit capisuite log files (finish with ':qa')\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -vh, --vh\fR: edit hylafax modem configuration file (finish with ':qa')\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -sqlv, --sql-verbose\fR: screen output with SQL commands (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -v, --verbose\fR: screen output more verbose\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -lfn, --logfilenew\fR: delete log file afore\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -cf, --conffile <string>\fR: uses configuration file <string> instead of ('\fB\fR')
.br
\fB -h, --help\fR: Explanation of frequent options\fB or not\fR (\fB3\fR)
.br
\fB -lh, --longhelp\fR: Explanation of all options\fB or not\fR (\fB3\fR)
.br
\fB -vi, --vi\fR: edit/view configuration file , log file etc. (finish with ':qa')\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -vs, --vs\fR: edit/view source files in \fB/home/schade/autofax2\fR(finish with ':qa')\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -ia, --interactive\fR: all parameters will be prompted (some of them not shown here)\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -noia, --nointeraction\fR: no questions, e.g. for a call from within cron\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -info, --version\fR: shows the program version\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fBOptions to be saved in the configuration file: (preced. '1'=don't save, 'no'=contrary, e.g. '-noocra','-1noocri'):\fR
.br
\fB -tdr, --tofaxdir <path>\fR: faxes the files from <path> instead of ('\fB/var/autofax2/tobefaxed\fR')
.br
\fB -wdr, --waitdir <path>\fR: files are waiting in <path> instead of ('\fB/var/autofax2/waitingfaxes\fR')
.br
\fB -ndr, --notfaxeddir <path>\fR: Failed Faxes are collected here and not in ('\fB/var/autofax2/notfaxed\fR')
.br
\fB -rdr, --receiveddir <path>\fR: directory for recieved faxes ('\fB/var/autofax2/recvdir\fR')
.br
\fB -fbox, --takefbox <zahl>\fR: use fritzbox\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
.br
\fB -fbdr, --fritzboxdir <path>\fR: receiving directory of the fritzbox (via CIFS) ('\fB/mnt/diabfb/Generic-FlashDisk-01/FRITZ/faxbox\fR')
.br
\fB -capi, --takecapi <zahl>\fR: use capisuite\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
.br
\fB -hyla, --takehyla <zahl>\fR: use hylafax\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
.br
\fB -hf, --hylafirst <zahl>\fR: trying to send faxes first via hylafax\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -fc, --firstcapi <zahl>\fR: try to send faxes primarily via capisuite\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -mod, --hmodem <string>\fR: Modem used for hylafax, instead of  ('\fBttyACM0\fR')
.br
\fB -mc, --maxcapitries <string>\fR: try Hylafax after <no> tries of Capisuite instead of ('\fB3\fR')
.br
\fB -mh, --maxhylatries <string>\fR: try Capisuite after <no> tries of Hylafax instead of ('\fB3\fR')
.br
\fB -cuser, --cuser <string>\fR: takes the linux user <string> for capisuite and/or samba instead of ('\fBschade\fR')
.br
\fB -crct, --cringcount <string>\fR: No. of bell rings until Capisuite accepts the call, instead of ('\fB1\fR')
.br
\fB -hrct, --hringcount <string>\fR: No. of bell rings until hylafaxs accepts the call, instead of ('\fB2\fR')
.br
\fB -hmd, --hmaxdials <string>\fR: No of dialing retries in hylafax, instead of   ('\fB11\fR')
.br
\fB -it, --immediatelytarget <zahl>\fR: copy faxes into target directory irrespective of faxing success\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
.br
\fB -ocri, --ocri <zahl>\fR: Text from received faxes will be filtered\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
.br
\fB -ocro, --ocro <zahl>\fR: Text from sent pictures will be filtered\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -tfs, --tofaxstr <string>\fR: the fax number will be expected after <string> instead of ('\fBan Fax\fR')
.br
\fB -tcfs, --tocfaxstr <string>\fR: fax no.for fax with preference to capisuite is expected after <string> instead of ('\fBan cFax\fR')
.br
\fB -thfs, --tohfaxstr <string>\fR: fax no.for fax with preference to hylafax is expected after <string> instead of ('\fBan hFax\fR')
.br
\fB -ts, --tostr <string>\fR: name of addressee is expected after <string> instead of ('\fB an \fR')
.br
\fB -ands, --andstr <string>\fR: separating string <string> for multiple addressees/tel'numbers, instead of ('\fBund\fR')
.br
\fB -fd, --find <string>\fR: version 1,2 or 3 of filefind (variable performance differences instead of ('\fB3\fR')
.br
\fB --1, ---1 <zahl>\fR: No.of the sql-commands for finding out senders (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB --1, ---1 <zahl>\fR: No of pairs of patterns/directories for saving received faxes (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -host, --host <string>\fR: takes the database on host <string> instead of ('\fBlocalhost\fR')
.br
\fB -muser, --muser <string>\fR: takes the user <string> for MySQL/MariaDB instead of ('\fBuser\fR')
.br
\fB -mpwd, --mpwd <string>\fR: takes the password <string> for MySQL/MariaDB
.br
\fB -db, --database <string>\fR: uses the database <string> instead of ('\fBfaxe\fR')
.br
\fB -lg, --language <string>\fR: Language/Sprache/Lingue/Lingua [\fBd\fReutsch,\fBe\fRnglisch] ('\fBe\fR')
.br
\fB -ldr, --logdir <path>\fR: choses <path> as log directory, currently ('\fB/var/log\fR')
.br
\fB -lf, --logfilename <string>\fR: log file <string> (in path '\fB/var/log\fR') will be used instead of ('\fBautofax2.log\fR')
.br
\fB -l, --log <zahl>\fR: put detailed logs in file '\fB/var/log/autofax2.log\fR' (otherwise shorter)\fB or not\fR (\fB0\fR)
.br
\fB -cm, --cronminutes <string>\fR: every how many minutes shall \fBautofax2\fR be called in crontab (0=not at all), instead of  ('\fB0\fR')
.br
\fB -autoupd, --autoupdate <zahl>\fR: Update program automatically\fB or not\fR (\fB1\fR)
